cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving the performance of datacenter networks using Multipath TCP (MPTCP) and SDN. The use of MPTCP and SDN in datacenter networks falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 

2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an MPTCP-aware SDN controller that facilitates an alternative routing mechanism for MPTCP subflows. This involves controlling the behavior of the network, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 

3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper briefly mentions the security implications of using MPTCP and SDN in datacenter networks. This falls under the scope of cryptography and security. 

4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper focuses on improving the performance of datacenter networks using MPTCP and SDN. This falls under the scope of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing. 

5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper briefly mentions the use of packet inspection to provide deterministic subflow assignment to paths. This falls under the scope of information theory, which deals with the transmission, processing, and utilization of information.
